PREREQUISITE: To view the documentation, you must have Docker
installed. For installation instructions, refer to the Docker 
documentation: https://docs.docker.com/engine/installation/

---------------------------------------------------------------

To launch the CNX documentation website:

1. Download the tigera_cnx-docs_v2.0.1.tar.xz file.

2. Import the file into your local Docker engine.

   ```
   docker load -i tigera_cnx-docs_v2.0.1.tar.xz
   ```
   
3. Type `docker images` to confirm that it has loaded and to get 
   the name of the image. It should be `/tigera/cnx-docs`.
   
4. Use the following command to remove any previous load the Docker image and launch
   the docs website.
   
   ```
   docker rm -f cnx-docs >/dev/null 2>&1; docker run -d -p 4000:4000 --name cnx-docs tigera/cnx-docs:v2.0.1
   ```
   
5. Paste the following path in your browser.

   ```
   http://localhost:4000
   ```
   
6. Enjoy!